cutState(MDGNode, MDGNode) - Method in class machine.MultiedgeFinateLogicMachine
Replace-cut: removes node1 and replaces it with node2.\n - node2 may be new/alien; it will be inserted if missing.\n - Incoming edges to node1 are rewired to node2.\n - Outgoing edges of node1 are inherited by node2.\n - Start/accept sets are updated accordingly.

MultiedgeFinateLogicMachine - Class in machine
Finite state machine M = (S, Σ, T, I, A)\n - S (states) and T (transitions) are stored in the underlying multiedge directed graph.\n - Σ (alphabet) is provided at construction time and is immutable.\n - I (start states) and A (final/accept states) are subsets of S.\n - ε transitions are represented with label == null.\n
